      "writtenOn": "2020-09-10T20:23:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Sounds like a good idea.  In this particular case we\u0027re sampling from a pre-rasterized picture shader tile under the hood, so it probably doesn\u0027t make much difference - but it could help with purely analytical shaders.\n\nI\u0027m assuming the unpremul intrinsic handles zero alpha and returns something \"sane\", right?  Regular displacement selectors are modulated back by alpha, so even if the unpremul result is garbage it should not matter.  But I\u0027m curious now what happens with the selector modes which force full coverage... they seem to work in testing, maybe we\u0027re just lucky with our unpremul/zero behavior choice.",
      "parentUuid": "da66970f_ef5e845d",
      "revId": "f3f166ce97d93fda3e7d6584266c1340ed2d7782",
